1
00:01:24,319 --> 00:01:25,000
Hey!

2
00:01:25,439 --> 00:01:26,439
It's red light.

3
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:27,599
You can only go when it turns green.

4
00:01:28,599 --> 00:01:29,079
Turn...

5
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:30,120
Turn green.

6
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:30,480
Hmm.

7
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:31,719
Zebra crossing.

8
00:01:31,719 --> 00:01:33,280
Stop at red light, go at green light.

9
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,640
What's a zebra?

10
00:01:36,879 --> 00:01:37,359
Hey!

11
00:02:02,599 --> 00:02:03,799
Xiao Chengjing might be right.

12
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,879
Let go of the past.

13
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:07,359
Start over.

14
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:15,159
What's this strange thing?

15
00:02:15,319 --> 00:02:16,120
The meat here

16
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:18,280
is different from what we've had before.

17
00:02:18,719 --> 00:02:19,719
I brought you here

18
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:21,639
to show you around.

19
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,960
Generally,

20
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,360
medium-rare steak is the best,

21
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:25,879
tender and juicy.

22
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:28,680
But the one I had last time was medium-well,

23
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:29,840
and it was also good.

24
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:30,599
So,

25
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:31,919
I ordered medium-well for you.

26
00:02:45,919 --> 00:02:46,360
Hello.

27
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:47,879
Could you get us two pairs of chopsticks?

28
00:02:47,879 --> 00:02:48,400
Sure.

29
00:02:51,439 --> 00:02:51,840
Here you go.

30
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:53,520
Use this.

31
00:02:58,800 --> 00:02:59,560
But I see

32
00:03:00,039 --> 00:03:01,120
everyone around here

33
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:01,919
is using this.

34
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,280
But...

35
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,439
It seems like no one is using chopsticks.

36
00:03:16,719 --> 00:03:18,080
Don't worry about what others think.

37
00:03:18,319 --> 00:03:19,599
Who said you can't use chopsticks?

38
00:03:24,319 --> 00:03:26,319
Don't be so concerned about what others think.

39
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:28,280
Who said you can't use chopsticks for steak?

40
00:03:49,319 --> 00:03:50,479
Order whatever you want.

41
00:03:50,599 --> 00:03:51,319
I want

42
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:52,960
this, this, this,

43
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,240
and this.

44
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:55,159
Oh, and this.

45
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:56,960
And this.

46
00:04:03,319 --> 00:04:03,879
Boss,

47
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,319
you're acting strange.

48
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:09,400
Did you have a fight with Ms. Yan?

49
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:11,120
Or

50
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:13,120
she stood you up?

51
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,759
That's why I got the good stuff.

52
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:18,120
But, boss, I'm not saying this.

53
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:21,000
Although Assistant Yan is usually careless,

54
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,800
after all, she is a girl.

55
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,879
You should care about her more.

56
00:04:24,279 --> 00:04:25,800
Don't let someone else take her away.

57
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,199
I haven't finished speaking.

58
00:04:29,439 --> 00:04:30,279
You pay for this meal.

59
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,279
Ah?

60
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:33,839
So,

61
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:36,600
the entrance to this world is the Qixi star chart.

62
00:04:37,199 --> 00:04:37,480
Yes.

63
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,720
Then how do we get back?

64
00:04:43,639 --> 00:04:44,319
I don't know.

65
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:45,879
That voice...

66
00:04:46,399 --> 00:04:47,040
Didn't say.

67
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:50,079
By the way,

68
00:04:51,319 --> 00:04:52,160
in a few days,

69
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:53,959
I want to introduce you to someone.

70
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:58,800
Who is it?

71
00:05:01,079 --> 00:05:02,000
Someone

72
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,439
very important to me.

73
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:08,759
The acquisition agreement of the company is being processed by the legal department.

74
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:09,959
I'm sure it will be done before Qixi Festival.

75
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,040
Okay.

76
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:13,759
Boss

77
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:15,680
Do you remember Li Si?

78
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,279
Li Si?

79
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:19,000
His new novel is a hit.

80
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,480
The board of directors has decided

81
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:23,120
to sign him back.

82
00:05:24,399 --> 00:05:26,079
But I've already probed his mind.

83
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,240
He has no grudges against our company.

84
00:05:28,839 --> 00:05:30,480
He is satisfied with the conditions we offer.

85
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,279
I've read his new novel.

86
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:33,600
It's a hollow frame.

87
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:35,720
It's full of his anger.

88
00:05:36,399 --> 00:05:37,399
It's meaningless.

89
00:05:38,519 --> 00:05:39,000
Boss,

90
00:05:39,519 --> 00:05:42,399
the board was already unhappy with our previous author removal,

91
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,279
and now Li Si is gaining popularity again.

92
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,279
If we refuse this time,

93
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:47,920
I'm worried

94
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:50,879
they'll bring up the author removal issue again.

95
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,120
Why are you back so late?

96
00:06:30,639 --> 00:06:31,839
Didn't I tell you

97
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,279
I was busy today?

98
00:06:33,279 --> 00:06:34,519
Busy on a date with someone else?

99
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:35,680
Hey, Xu Chi,

100
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:37,279
Are you free tomorrow?

101
00:06:37,279 --> 00:06:37,920
No.

102
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,560
Hey, something's wrong with you.

103
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,800
Why do you sound like a complaining woman?

104
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:44,600
Do I?

105
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,279
Yes.

106
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,160
By the way,

107
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:49,639
I saw a kid

108
00:06:49,639 --> 00:06:51,480
holding this lollipop in the park today.

109
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:52,160
Here you are.

110
00:06:52,639 --> 00:06:53,720
You went to the park?

111
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,000
Yes.

112
00:06:55,839 --> 00:06:57,319
Don't you have anything to tell me?

113
00:06:58,199 --> 00:06:58,759
Yes.

114
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:01,519
I want to invite you to dinner tomorrow.

115
00:07:02,879 --> 00:07:03,399
What for?

116
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:05,959
You said you wanted me to have dinner with you.

117
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:06,759
It's too late.

118
00:07:07,199 --> 00:07:08,240
I'm very busy recently.

119
00:07:08,519 --> 00:07:08,920
I have no time.

120
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,079
Well.

121
00:07:16,839 --> 00:07:17,439
It depends on my mood.

122
00:07:24,519 --> 00:07:26,240
I'll take you to meet him tomorrow night.

123
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:28,000
It's the same place where we had dinner yesterday.

124
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,160
I don't have any other problems here.

125
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:34,800
The contract

126
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:36,000
is signed tomorrow.

127
00:07:36,839 --> 00:07:37,360
Tomorrow?

128
00:07:38,319 --> 00:07:39,759
Mr. Li said it can only be tomorrow.

129
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,839
Then let's make it tomorrow noon.

130
00:07:44,639 --> 00:07:46,000
I have an important date tonight.
